<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/123763426-rachel-cole"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/123763426-rachel-cole">Rachel Cole</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I loved the whole series. I thought the quality was consistent, so if you liked one you would like them all. The first three (nightingale, grass, moon<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I loved the whole series. I thought the quality was consistent, so if you liked one you would like them all. The first three (nightingale, grass, moon) sort of go together in a trilogy. The 4th (heron) takes place 15 years after the end of the third book and the 5th (heaven's net) is a prequel. You could stop after the first three if you are satisfied, or keep going if you want to delve more into the world. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

