        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2596533504" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3413819212148685955">This is a light Feudal Japanese fantasy that focuses heavily on growing up to be an assassin, trembling with desire and love, and reveals that drive the main character to dire measures.<br/><br/>Does most of this sound familiar in YA fiction? It should. :)<br/><br/>Fortunately, I enjoy light Feudal Japanese fantasies... NARUTO!!! and while this is fairly light on the magic, (sorry, Naruto fans,) the writing is comfortable and predictable and I can firmly put this in the comfort-food category of literature.<br/><br/>Special t</span>
  <span id="freeText3413819212148685955" style="display:none">This is a light Feudal Japanese fantasy that focuses heavily on growing up to be an assassin, trembling with desire and love, and reveals that drive the main character to dire measures.<br /><br />Does most of this sound familiar in YA fiction? It should. :)<br /><br />Fortunately, I enjoy light Feudal Japanese fantasies... NARUTO!!! and while this is fairly light on the magic, (sorry, Naruto fans,) the writing is comfortable and predictable and I can firmly put this in the comfort-food category of literature.<br /><br />Special things of note... lots of assassination training and experience! A love story for the ages! Loveable mentors falling to force big decisions on main characters! <br /><br />Sigh... at least I like this kind of thing. :)</span>
