<span id="freeTextContainer16569025658508720209">A great series about ancient Japan with its samurais and their conduct codes, ninja-like fighters, Christians&apos; persecutions; it has political scheming, interesting twists and turns, intriguing liaisons between characters, sword fights, love, treachery, friendship. <br/>The characters are well-developed, complex, with inner turmoil and weaknesses.<br/><br/>The only thing that disappointed me was the romance element, exaggerated a tad too much in my opinion: when she first laid eyes on him, she started trembling</span>
  <span id="freeText16569025658508720209" style="display:none">A great series about ancient Japan with its samurais and their conduct codes, ninja-like fighters, Christians' persecutions; it has political scheming, interesting twists and turns, intriguing liaisons between characters, sword fights, love, treachery, friendship. <br />The characters are well-developed, complex, with inner turmoil and weaknesses.<br /><br />The only thing that disappointed me was the romance element, exaggerated a tad too much in my opinion: when she first laid eyes on him, she started trembling, became feverish and knew she cannot live without him..<blockquote>
  <i>“The less people think of you, the more they will reveal to you or in your presence.” <br /><br />“I believe the test of government is the contentment of the people.”</i>
</blockquote></span>
