              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2784008979237130302">Mini-Review:<br/><br/>Narration: <br/>Kevin Gray - 3 Stars: Removed narration style that made the story seem emotionless. Somewhat odd, whispery narration voice. Overall, it seemed like he was bored &amp; not engaged by the story he narrated. <br/>Aiko Nakasone - 4 Stars: Pleasant voice &amp; well intoned, emotional nuance. <br/>Intro/Ending Music: The music should be played before or after narration. Not on top of narration. <br/><br/>The story is about a young man that survived a brutal attack. He is taken in by a man of power and trai</span>
  <span id="freeText2784008979237130302" style="display:none">Mini-Review:<br /><br />Narration: <br />Kevin Gray - 3 Stars: Removed narration style that made the story seem emotionless. Somewhat odd, whispery narration voice. Overall, it seemed like he was bored &amp; not engaged by the story he narrated. <br />Aiko Nakasone - 4 Stars: Pleasant voice &amp; well intoned, emotional nuance. <br />Intro/Ending Music: The music should be played before or after narration. Not on top of narration. <br /><br />The story is about a young man that survived a brutal attack. He is taken in by a man of power and trained to follow into a web of politics that he doesn't understand. It's also about a young girl that has only ever been a pawn for her family and foes. They met and fall in love. <br /><br />While the broad strokes of the plot were interesting, there was a decided lack in details to make the story come to life. There wasn't enough description about either main characters lives or actions. You get some introspection, lots of short summaries, spurts of active scenes and the book ends. <br /><br />Pros:<br />- There are elegant lines and phrases that describe emotion, thoughts or setting. <br />- Main plot points has potential for an epic story. <br />- Fitting title for first book.<br /><br />Cons:<br />- Dual POV: Male POV was ok &amp; had sparks of great writing. Female POV was flat and not interesting except to establish plot points. <br />- Sparse writing style: The chosen style did not work well throughout the book. There were moments of great writing &amp; meaning, but the rest was a string of summaries and statements of action. <br /><br />Note to Self: Library has some of the books in the series. Read via library loans. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2784008979237130302" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


